deal_with_the_shaki_naibs_title;Resolving the issue of the Shaki Naibs;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
deal_with_the_shaki_naibs_desc;During the turbulent times of Persian and Turkoman rule, Eastern Armenia saw wide-spread settlement of Turkomans, turning the once faily homogenous land into a multicultural crossroad in the Caucasus. The Shaki and their predecessors assigned nobles, the so-called naibs, to govern their territories on a local level and even now they still control half our territory. Their loyalty to Erivan is tenous at best. Members of the Armenian aristocracy and bureaucracy have proposed that we try to break their hold onto these territories, as their militaristic background causes them to do precious little of economic worth with it. Ending their ownership could open up many possiblities of economic development and renewed Armenian settlement of the regions. How are we to deal with this issue?;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
invite_armenian_diaspora_title;Invite the Armenian Diaspora;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
invite_armenian_diaspora_desc;The many wars that ravaged the Caucasus left deep scars for the Armenian people. Since the late XVI century regular emigration waves left the Armenian community constantly shrinking. As a result, the land become partially depopulated and less homogenous, but abroad Armenian culture continued to flourish in many European communities. Now that the homeland is restored, we should invite this diaspora back home, so that it may revitalise our national identity and share with us the western knowledge they acquired over multiple generations.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
irrigate_armenia_title;Irrigate the Armenian valleys;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
irrigate_armenia_desc;The Armenian economy of the XVIII and XIX century was mainly based on pastoralism, with the exception of copper-mining which has been conducted ever since prehistoric times. But even farming has proven to be rather difficult in many areas of the country, as arid conditions are prevalent. Luckily for us, the solution to this problem resides directly above us in the mountains of the Caucasus. Now that we have the technology necessary for such a project, we can begin  the large-scale irrigation of the valleys. With this system in place, we could finally satisfy the needs of industrial agriculture and take our first steps in properly industrialising Armenia!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
settle_national_borders_armenia_title;Settle the Armenian Borders;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
settle_national_borders_armenia_desc;Ever since the fall of the last Armenian kingdom, the national borders for a new Armenian state have always been a matter of debate. Now that Armenia emerged from the shadows and became increasingly akin to its Christian relatives in Europe, it ought to properly resolve this issue like they would. If it truly seeks to become a western nation-state, it should try to encompass all Armenians in the region and not let geography define its borders as it was the case in the past. To the west we should force our way to the Black Sea, to the east we should press our claim to Karabakh, origin of our royal house and home to many of our Armenian brothers, still under Turkoman tyranny. Only once we have claimed these territories, our kingdom will truly be worthy to call itself sovereign over Armenia!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
proclaim_greater_armenia_title;Proclaim Greater Armenia;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
proclaim_greater_armenia_desc;In the last decades we have worked hard to make the dream of a free Armenian nation reality and we have truly come far. However there are still many Armenians living beyond our borders, many of them subject to the oppression of the Ottoman Turks. Bringing these territories into our country would ensure that their religious and cultural freedom would be respected. And while it would put us back into direct conflict with the Ottoman Empire and bring many foreigners into our country, it is a preferable alternative to continue watching how our kin is slowly but surely silenced and eroded from the face of these lands.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
restore_empire_of_tigranes_title;Restore the Empire of Tigranes the Great;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
restore_empire_of_tigranes_desc;The war over Cilicia has proven that even after all we have accomplished there will always be need for a protector of all Armenians and Christendom in the Near East. To that end we must lead our nation to its greatest heights and beyond, so that nobody will dare to threaten our kin again! Our ancestors once brought about an Armenian golden age under their king Tigranes the Great. And to this day none of our polities managed to ever exceed his Empire. It is only logical that we ought to build our eternal Armenia in the image of Tigranes' Empire! Then and only then will the reign of eagle and lion remain unbroken!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
end_ottoman_imperialism_anatolia_title;End Ottoman Imperialism in the East;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
end_ottoman_imperialism_anatolia_desc;For too long we suffered under the Ottoman imperialist yoke! Even now that we have liberated most of our people, there are still many more that suffer the same fate we once did! How could we accept peace with a system that seeks the total eradication of our brothers in chains? We will liberate the opressed souls of Anatolia once and for all, so that they may finally live in peace and equality!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
accept_assyrians_title;Integrate the Assyrians;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
accept_assyrians_desc;As our Empire grows, it is housing an ever-increasing number of peoples. Many of those have been subject to the same horrors and supression as we once did. Amongst them the Assyrians of northern Mesopotamia, who had suffered for centuries under foreign muslim rule and were especially persecuted during the chaos of the Ottoman civil war. As we are not just protectors of all Armenians, but Christendom in the Middle East in general, we have good reason to grant them the same rights and privileges as the common Armenian citizen! Such an act would also strenghten our control of the Mesopotamian provinces, where our presence is still rather limited.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
accept_syriacs_title;Integrate the Syriacs;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
accept_syriacs_desc;With the ancient fortress of Antioch being in our control, we also have established contact with the venerable Syriac Orthodox Church seated there and by extension the other Christian communities in the Levante. The Syriacs or Arameans have been subjected to the same terrors as we once were and as we are protectors of all the supressed Christians in the Near East, it is our duty to accept them into our ranks as equal citizens of our Empire! This would strengthen our southern border and even open up the possibility for further expansion southwards into the Levante!;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
accept_georgians_title;Integrate the Georgians;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
accept_georgians_desc;Throughout the times of foreign invasion, we could not rely on many allies. But amongst the few were mainly our Georgian neighbours, who had to face the same hardship as we did. When the Shaki invaded the Christian territories of the Caucasus, we allied the Georgian principalities and fought and fell by their side. Now that our national borders are settled, we find ourselves with many Georgians in our northern regions. They should not be treated like they were under the Shaki or Ottoman, which is why we will integrate them into the political life of our nation.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
armenian_turkish_population_exchange_treaty_title;Treaty for the Turko-Armenian Population Exchange;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
armenian_turkish_population_exchange_treaty_desc;With the rise of Armenian nationalism and the creation of an expansionist Armenian state, the balance of power in Anatolia has been destroyed. The Armenians and Turks are now locked in a bitter rivalry and ethnic tension in both countries are at an all-time high. The only lasting solution would be a population exchange of Armenian and Turkish populations. While this drastic measure might be the only way to ensure lasting peace in Anatolia, it will also solidify the current border and take away our opportunity to reclaim the land of our people. Should we start negotiations with the other party?;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;; 
create_georgia_title;Create Georgia;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
create_georgia_desc;After the collapse of the last united Georgian realm in the XVI century, the region has been traditionally divided into the three principalities of Samtskhe, Imereti and Kartli. As they were under constant domination by foreign powers, none of the three ever managed to reunite the realm, but that does not mean that the dream of a united Georgia is lost. By bringing the territory under our control and granting one of the princes the crown for Georgia, we could create a valuable ally and strengthen our position in the Caucasus significantly.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
return_capital_shiraz_title;Move the Capital Back to Shiraz;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
return_capital_shiraz_desc;Now that the Qashqai and Lurish rebels have been defeated, Shiraz, the City of Flowers and Nightingale, can be once more the seat of our political power. With the power of the Qashqai Confederacy broken, we shall take the opportunity to reform the toll system of this trade hub and increase the prosperity of our Capital.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
move_capital_rasht_title;Move the Capital to Rasht;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
move_capital_rasht_desc;Although Lahijan has been the centre of political power in Gilan for centuries, the economical pole has over time decisively moved to Rasht. The westernmost city in the Kar-Kiya domains, Rasht has attracted a large foreigner community, serving as a trade hub for goods sailing across the Caspian Sea or coming overland from Baku and Tbilisi. Furthermore, Rasht was the cradle of the Constitutional Revolution that ended the despotic powers of the Kiya Amirs. Moving our capital to Rasht would reflect the economic realities of our state, as well as symbolising a clean break with the old absolutist regime.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
encourage_tea_lahijan_title;Encourage Tea Plantations in Lahijan;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
encourage_tea_lahijan_desc;After the disruptions caused by the Janissary Revolt, western for silk was rerouted to India, and although trouble in Anatolia has died down, this vital source of currency has not returned to Gilan. One of our diplomats, recently returned from the distant lands of Hendustan, claims to have found a solution to our problems - he has smuggled tea seedlings which, he claims, would grow perfectly on the hills surrounding Lahijan. Tea is an opportunity to regain the West as a trading partner, and finally provide the state with a reliable source of income with which to finance reforms.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
liberate_caspians_title;Liberate the Azerbaijani Iranians;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
liberate_caspians_desc;The lands south of the Aras river are home to numerous Fahlavi Iranians, who have obstinately retained their culture for centuries in the face of waves of Turkic migrations. In the aftermath of the collapse of the Timurtash Empire, the former vassal Khan of Tabriz was absorbed by the Shaki Turkomans, seizing in one stroke the third largest city of Iran and the former Timurtash logistical depot for campaigns westwards to Anatolia or northwards to the Caucasus. It is time to push to the Aras river, liberate Tabriz and free our Caspian brothers from Turkoman opression.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
fund_nationalist_anjoman_title;Fund Nationalist Anjomans;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
fund_nationalist_anjoman_desc;One of the pillars of the Constitutional Revolution was nationalism - the driving desire to unify the Iranian lands under a strong nation state instead of division between squabbling dynasties. The ministry of Interior has devised a scheme to bring this about: fund nationalist Anjomans, secret para-military societies, outside of our borders to sow dissent and pave the ground for our takeover. Although bordering on state-terrorism, this unorthodox solution might yet avoid greater bloodshed in the inevitable unification of Iran.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
train_daylamite_mountain_troops_title;Train Daylamite Mountain Troops;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
train_daylamite_mountain_troops_desc;The Daylamites are a rugged people living in the Alborz mountain range separating Gilan and Mazanderan from the rest of the Iranian plateau. Being tough people accustomed to traversing difficult mountain trails, the Daylamites are ideal candidates to raise regiments specialised in mountain warfare. The creation of the Mountain Troops will give us an invaluable asset to wage war in the Iranian plateau, itself crossed by the Zagros, Alborz and Kopet Dag ranges - as well as any future campaigns that we might launch in the Caucasus.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
kar_kiya_land_reform_title;Redistribute the Kar-Kiya Crown Lands;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
kar_kiya_land_reform_desc;The peasants largely supported the Constitutionalists during the Revolution, enticed by promises of a wide-ranging land reform to break up the large landed estates of the Kar-Kiya crown lands and redistribute them to the peasantry. As these promises fail to materialise, unrest continues to grow in the countryside. Some of the progressive members of the Majles now begin to see this looming issue as an opportunity - by redistributing the crown lands, the power of the landed nobility will be broken, thus fatally weakening one of the pillars of the conservative oppostion.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
persecute_twelvers_ismailis_title;Persecute the Twelver and Ismaili Herectics;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
persecute_twelvers_ismailis_desc;Shayk Zahed has proclaimed that the agitation caused by the followers of the Twelver and Ismaili branches of Shi'a Islam shall be brought to a swift end. They insist on refusing to acknowledge the Zaydi Shayk as the rightful Imam, the Ismailis following instead a line of irrelevant Qasimid paupers, and the Twelvers going even further in their heresy claiming the rightful Imam to be in Occultation, waiting for an auspicious time to return. By resisting Zahed's omniscient edicts, Twelvers and Ismailis have shown themselves to be enemies of the true believers, and the enemy of a believer is the enemy of God, and the enemy of God is an infidel - and shall be treated accordingly.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
avenge_karbala_title;Avenge the Martyrs of Karbala;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
avenge_karbala_desc;The martyrdom of Husayn ibn Ali at Karbala is the defining moment of the Shi'a branch of Islam. Revolting against the Sunni Umayyads to reclaim his rightful position of Caliph, being a descendent of the Prophet, his death and the massacre of his followers at Karbala awakened the Muslim community to the oppressive nature of Umayyad rule. 1200 years later, a Sunni dynasty is again oppressing the Shi'ites of Iraq, making it a moral imperative for us to wield the sword of Ali against those who dare to bring suffering to the Shi'a faithful.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
secure_khorasani_shrines_title;Secure the Khorasani Shrines;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
secure_khorasani_shrines_desc;Hasan al-Urtush was a Zaydi missionary who tried to spread the faith to Khorasan, earning him imprisonment and torture by the Khorasani Amir in Nishapur. Although deafend, al-Urtush would go on to convert the fire-worshiping Daylamites and Gilakis to Zaydi Islam and found the Zaydi Imamate. Shrines honoring these feats dot Khorasan from Nishapur to Marw, though they are in a state of disrepair due to the carlessness of the local rulers, who, as back in the time of al-Urtush's Samanid antagonists, follow the Sunni faith. It is time for us to administer the region directly and pay proper honour to Hasan al-Urtush's legacy.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
zaydi_yemen_protectorate_title;Bring the Imamate to the Gulf of Aden;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
zaydi_yemen_protectorate_desc;Before Zahed's rebellion spread the Zaydi fath to all of Iran, the only other part of the world where the true faith was professed was Yemen. The northern highlands of Yemen were converted to Zaydism in 893 by Yahya bin al-Husayn, establishing a community that would struggle over the centuries for ascendancy with its southern Sunni neighbours. The current rulers of Yemen patronise Sunnism, and the resulting marginalisation of Zaydis and the frequent sectarian violence directed against them is an affront to anyone professing to be a pious Muslim. We shall bring the Imamate to the shores of the Gulf of Aden - by force, if necessary.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
integrate_khaliji_arabs_title;Integrate the Khaliji Arabs;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
integrate_khaliji_arabs_desc;Although the Zaydi Yemenites have been brought into our fold, the administration of the area is still in the hands of Iranians coming from the mainland, causing resentment among the local population. Integrating the Khaliji Arabs, the majority in the Zaydi community of Yemen, into the administrative apparatus of the Protectorate would greatly increase our standing among the natives, as well as opening up prospects of further expansion north into the Holy Sites of Mecca and Medina.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
kar_kiya_modernise_army_title;Reform the Army on Western Lines;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
kar_kiya_modernise_army_desc;It is clear that if Iran is to survive in the current context of European Imperial competition in Asia, it needs an army capable of facing the foreigners in their own terms. The presence of the Russian military attaché in our capital provides us with an opportunity to bring this to reality. The Shah has decreed the training of the Reformed Army, the Mezam-e Jadid - importing Russian officers to drill the infantry, sending Iranian officers abroad to be instructed in Russia, setting up foundries to produce artillery and opening a polytechnic school to train military engineers.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
treaty_amol_title;The Treaty of Amol;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
treaty_amol_desc;After a grueling campaign we have managed to decisively beat the Russians and eject them from their forts at Gorgan and Bandar Torkaman. In spite of the mining of our Gilaki-Mazanderani ports, the Russians have been unable to keep our raiding vessels permanently in port and therefore prevent the disruption of the already tenuous supply lines across the Caspian Sea. Moreover, disease has ravaged the Russian's ranks, most soldiers being unused to the harsh climate of Golestan. The Russian government now seems receptive to ending the war diplomatically, lest they suffer even more embarassing losses.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
inflame_caucasus_jihad_title;Instigate Rebellion in the Caucasus;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
inflame_caucasus_jihad_desc;In our present struggle against the Russians we will need all the help we can possibly muster. Such support might be forcoming from the Caucasus, where the population resents the opressive Russian rule. Guerrillas are already being organised by the Sufi Order operating in the region, the Naqshbandiya, led by a charismatic Shayk preaching resistance to his fellow mountain people. We should send agents to Dagestan to bring about the staging of a general uprising by the Naqshbandis, who are eager to wage Jihad, thus opening a new front in the rear of the Russian forces and dirupting their overland supply lines through the Caucasus mountain passes.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
treaty_argos_title;The Treaty of Argos;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
treaty_argos_desc;For three years the Venetians have tried in vain to stamp out the dream of Greek freedom. Now, after having been completely driven out from Attica and the Morea and having almost completely exhausted the treasury of the Serenissima, the Venetians are finally ready to acknowledge defeat and recognise the Independence of the Hellenic Republic. The liberation of Greece will not be complete - the Venetians will keep possession of the Aegean Islands - but our young republic has also been driven to the verge of collapse over the course of the war. A general amnesty on both sides will be declared, and both Republics have pledged themselves to protect and respect the numerous minorities that will now find themselves on the wrong side of the new border.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
settle_ioannina_title;Propose a Population Exchange with Albania;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
settle_ioannina_desc;Northern Epirus has been a bone of contention between Albania and Greece ever since both nations gained independence from the Ottoman Empire and Venice. Hellenes and Albanians live intermingled on both sides of the present border, with Albanians being a majority around Gjirokaster and Greeks being predominant around Ioannina. Given the impossiblity of drawing clear ethnic boundaries in the lands between these two cities, our diplomats have approached the Albanian government with a proposal to end Greco-Albanian animosity forever: the border between the two nations will be drawn along the lines of the former Ottoman Sanjak of Yanina, and any Greeks north or Albanians south of this border will have to migrate to their new homeland.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
claim_taurica_title;Claim Taurica;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
claim_taurica_desc;Greek presence in Taurica, currently known by its Turkic name Crimea, dates back to the 5th Century BCE. It was Greek enterpreneurs who founded the port cities of Sebastopol and Theodosia, who erected impressive fortifications at Taphros and Chersonesus Trachea and built the powerful Bosporan Kingdom of antiquity - yet this legacy is now all but forgotten after centuries of Turkic domination have practically erased the Hellenic heritage of Taurica. It is time to reclaim what's rightfully ours.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
timurtash_protect_ismaili_title;Legalise the Activity of the Ismaili Da'i;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
timurtash_protect_ismaili_desc;The Da'i, the missionaries of the Ismaili faith, have come under increasing pressure in the last few decades, being accused of building a network of Assassins in the Timurtash Empire. Such fanciful stories are used by the Dehqans to shift away the blame of the violent political climate of Khorasan, forcing an already secretive community further into concealment. In truth, the Da'i only seek to educate the members of the Ismaili community in religious doctrine and, seldomly, win worthy new converts. The Ismaili madrasas teach not only theology, but also a miriad of secular subjects, and the tradition of preserving Ismaili heritage through manuscript study has kept literacy levels high within the community. It is in our best interest to protect the Da'i, and therefore the educative task they perform, even if that means infringing on the Dehqans administrative privileges.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
timurtash_idris_tribute_title;Force Idris Timurtash to Pay Tribute;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
timurtash_idris_tribute_desc;In a wanton act of defiance, the brother of the current Shahanshah, Idris, has refused to pay tribute for the past few years. Being the holder of the Soyurghal over the oases of Merv and Tejen, as well as the middle Murghab valley, Idris owes Firuz II a considerable sum of money. Aside from the humiliation of not recieving the annual tribute, the Timurtash court is rife with rumours of diplomatic feelers between Idris and the Uzbek Khan of Khwarezm to start a joint campaign against Firuz II. We must proceed swiftly and decidedly to subjugate Idris Timurtash, for a Civil War, in the current dire circumstances that the Empire finds itself in, could very well mean the end of the dynasty.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
irrigate_marw_herat_title;Improve the Irrigation Systems of Marw and Herat;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
irrigate_marw_herat_desc;Much of the irrigation system which fed the cultivated areas in the environs of Herat and in the oasis of Marw were ruined during the Dzunghar invasion and the ensuing struggle for power in Khorasan. With the canals in a state of disrepair, the Imperial treasury empty and the political authority of the Shahanshah waning, the hitherto lush orchards and extensive farmfields have decayed and the desert has started to creep back in. Nevertheless, if we undertake an ambitious project to repair the existing irrigation system and build new canals, the situation can be reversed. With the proposed plans, the agrarian economy of Khorasan will be strengthened by increasing the acreage under cultivation and will be diversified by promoting not only cereals and fruits but also vegetables, legumes, nuts and even flowers.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
abolish_mosallamiyat_title;Abolish the Mosallamiyat;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
abolish_mosallamiyat_desc;In the aftermath of the disastrous defeats against the Dzunghars and the Ottomans, the demoralised fragments of the Timurtash army could only be kept loyal to the Shahanshah through naked bribery. In lieu of monetary incentives - out of question given the desolate state of the Imperial treasury - generals and high-ranking officers were instead enticed with hereditary tax immunities, the Mosallamiyat. Although these measures kept the army away from mutiny and rebellion, if we are to rebuild the Imperial bureaucracy the tax base needs to be expanded and the Mosallamiyat privileges need to be abolished. Such a measure will certainly not be popular among our officer corps, who have over time acquired appanages of their own and become influential Dehqans in their own right.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
reestablish_imperial_amirs_title;Reestablish the Imperial Right to Appoint Amirs;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
reestablish_imperial_amirs_desc;In the Soyurghal system power is shared between the holder of the appanage and an amir, whose function is to supervise the administration and military forces of the Dehqan. Before the near-collapse of the Timurtash Empire amirs were appointed by Herat, reported directly to the Shahanshah and were therefore the link subordinating the Soyurghals to the Imperial centre. The erosion of central authority and decentralisation that followed the military defeats led to the amirs being chosen by the Dehqans themselves, greatly increasing their autonomy and their ability to disregard - or even act against - Imperial policy. Reestablishing the Imperial right to apoint amirs to the Soyurghals will allow us to conduct military and fiscal audits of the appanages and will represent a key milestone towards rebuilding the bureaucracy of the Empire.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
abolish_soyurghal_title;Abolish the Soyurghal System;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
abolish_soyurghal_desc;The Soyurghal system of land grants had been relegated to a largely ceremonial role by the 17th Century, with appanages being handed out only to close relatives of the Shahanshah and particularly the heir apparent. The threatening disintegration after the loss of Transoxiana and Western Iran breathed new life into the Soyurghal system, which was granted to the landed magnates of Khorasan, the Dehqans, as a way to tie their prosperity to the continued existance of the Timurtash Empire. Although catastrophe was staved off, the judicial and fiscal independence of the Soyurghals is an obstacle to the restoration of Imperial rule over Iran - for the Shahanshah cannot order, just encourage, the Dehqans to contribute to the overall military forces of the Empire. The Soyurghal system has outlived its usefulness, and it is high time that the Dehqans lose their privileges and are forced to acknowledge the supremacy of Herat.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
restore_hindukush_frontier_title;Restore the Old Timurtash-Dehli Frontier;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
restore_hindukush_frontier_desc;The old Timurtash frontier with the Sultanate of Dehli used to run along the Hindu Kush southwards towards the great trade emporium connecting India with Iran - Kandahar. Kandahar was the trade mart where indigo, textiles and sugar were imported to Iran, and war horses were exported to India. Its importance meant that over the centuries its possession was a source of conflict between the Timurtash Empire and Dehli, although it would remain largely in the hands of the former until the Dzunghar invasions. The collapse of the Timurtash armies in the Caucasus and the loss of Transoxiana gave an opportunity to the Karlani Pashtus, who had carved out a power base in Punjab, to strike southwards, conquer Kandahar, and then westwards across the Hindu Kush, conquering eastern Khorasan up to the gates of Herat. With Timurtash power back on the rise, it would be strategically sound to push the Afghans back and restore the old eastern frontier.;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
reclaim_mawarannahr_title;Reclaim Mawara an-Nahr;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
reclaim_mawarannahr_desc;Mawara an-Nahr - known as Transoxiana in the West - has traditionally been the heart of Timurtash power. Containing the rich oases of Khwarezm and the busy merchant hubs of Sogdiana and Tokharestan, Mawara an-Nahr was essential both as an extensive tax-base close to Herat and as home to a loyal and economically-dynamic sedentary Persian population. Complacency and protracted conflict with the Ottomans in the West led to the Timurtash military planners to consider Mawara an-Nahr as a safe province", a misjudgement that almost proved to be fatal when the Dzunghar Khanate rose from the ashes of the Chagatai and overran the Timurtash lands up to the Amu Darya. If the Timurtash Empire is to recover from its nadir, Mawara an-Nahr is to be re-incorporated into the Imperial demesne without delay.
